2

00:00:01,580  -->  00:00:04,020
it's important to be aware of the common pitfalls

3

00:00:04,020  -->  00:00:06,700
that can cause unexpected behavior in your code.

4

00:00:06,700  -->  00:00:10,600
Let's look at three key issues when it comes to writing our loops and Python.

5

00:00:10,600  -->  00:00:13,320
The first one, one by one errors

6

00:00:13,320  -->  00:00:17,780
occur when the loop iterates one too many times or too few.

7

00:00:17,780  -->  00:00:21,505
This often happens due to a misconfigured loop condition.

8

00:00:21,505  -->  00:00:23,810
Always ensure that your loops, range,

9

00:00:23,810  -->  00:00:26,990
or condition matches the number of iterations you expect,

10

00:00:26,990  -->  00:00:29,910
meaning the number of times you expect your code to run.

11

00:00:29,910  -->  00:00:32,970
Next step is with editing loop variables.

12

00:00:32,970  -->  00:00:38,230
Modifying the loop variable within the loop can lead to unexpected behavior.

13

00:00:38,230  -->  00:00:40,970
This makes the code harder to understand and

14

00:00:40,970  -->  00:00:43,990
may cause the loop to behave in unintended ways.

15

00:00:43,990  -->  00:00:48,070
It's best to avoid altering the loop variable directly inside the loop,

16

00:00:48,070  -->  00:00:50,490
but rather edit it outside of the loop,

17

00:00:50,490  -->  00:00:53,725
and then just have your loop run the code as expected.

18

00:00:53,725  -->  00:00:56,820
Finally, let's talk about mutable sequences.

19

00:00:56,820  -->  00:01:00,300
When iterating over mutable sequences like lists,

20

00:01:00,300  -->  00:01:05,180
be very cautious if you're modifying the sequence directly during the iteration.

21

00:01:05,180  -->  00:01:07,960
Doing so can result in skipped items as

22

00:01:07,960  -->  00:01:11,760
the loop might not account for changes made to the sequence.

23

00:01:11,760  -->  00:01:15,800
A good practice is to iterate over a copy of the sequence instead.

24

00:01:15,800  -->  00:01:19,000
This might seem like a lot to grasp at first, but don't worry.

